question: Determine the founding date of the International Hydrographic Organization; using the determined date, identify the major international conference convened months thereafter whose defining outcome was a landmark naval agreement among principal maritime powers, and specify that outcome.
solver_answer: The International Hydrographic Organization was founded on June 21, 1921. Months thereafter, the Washington Naval Conference (November 12, 1921 – February 6, 1922) produced the Washington Naval Treaty (Five-Power Treaty) on February 6, 1922, establishing landmark limits on naval armaments among principal maritime powers.
